  "16-18": (
    caption: [Biological tethers. The cofactors lipoate, biotin, and the combination of b-mercaptoethylamine and pantothenate form long, flexible arms (blue) on the enzymes to which they are covalently bound, acting as tethers that move intermediates from one active site to the next. The group shaded light red is in each case the point of attachment of the activated intermediate to the tether.],
    path: "../fig/image_place_holder.png"
