    caption: [A mutant isocitrate dehydrogenase acquires a new activity. Wild-type isocitrate dehydrogenase catalyzes the conversion of isocitrate to a-ketoglutarate, but mutations that alter the binding site for isocitrate cause loss of the normal enzymatic activity and gain of a new activity: conversion of a-ketoglutarate to 2-hydroxyglutarate. Accumulation of this product inhibits histone demethylase, altering gene regulation and leading to glial cell tumors in the brain.],
