  "16-25": (
    caption: [Coordinated regulation of glyoxylate and citric acid cycles. Regulation of isocitrate dehydrogenase activity determines the partitioning of isocitrate between the glyoxylate and citric acid cycles. When the enzyme is inactivated by phosphorylation (by a specific protein kinase), isocitrate is directed into biosynthetic reactions via the glyoxylate cycle. When the enzyme is activated by dephosphorylation (by a specific phosphatase), isocitrate enters the citric acid cycle and ATP is produced.],
